The paper deals with the problem of syntax-guided synthesis, which is a subfield of programming languages (cs.PL). The proposed method involves reducing the unrealizability problem to a reachability problem, which is a common technique in formal methods and logic (cs.LO). The paper also discusses the implementation of a tool called NOPE, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). Additionally, the paper deals with the problem of optimizing synthesized programs with respect to syntactic cost, which is related to formal languages (cs.FL). Finally, the paper involves the use of program-analysis tools, which is a subfield of software engineering and programming languages (cs.SC).
